<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="130" pageId="1" pageNumber="128" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1444,2009]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,392]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="129" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,484,1984,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">
Description of 
<typeStatus box="[381,484,1984,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">holotype</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[500,568,1984,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">Male.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[578,639,1984,2009]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[657,726,1984,2009]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1585,1608]" captionTargetBox="[316,1276,453,1557]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[302,1284,445,1564]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Drepanosticta seramensis sp. nov. (1) head and thorax, lateral view [holotype male]; (2) anal appendages, ventrolateral view [holotype male]; (3) anal appendages, dorsal view [holotype male]; (4) head and thorax, lateral view [allotype female]; (5) ovipositor, lateral view [allotype female]; (6) wings [holotype male]." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1459924/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Labium dark yellow, with brown markings (presumably by discoloration); labrum, mandibles and anteclypeus shiny pale cream, possibly bluish in living specimens; labrum with anterior half dark brown, dark stripe tapering towards antero-lateral corners; mandibles with anterior one-sixth dark brown; gena yellowish; rest of head brown, semi-matt, but postocular lobe and occiput distinctly paler; a conspicuous pale transverse stripe between antennae, somewhat constricted at level of anterior ocellus; fine longitudinal striae between eyes and lateral ocelli; rest of head coriaceous; transverse occipital carina poorly developed, without lateral extremities. Antennae with scapus pale brown at base, rest of scapus and pedicellus pale cream; flagellum brown (right flagellum broken). Eyes in preserved specimen middle brown.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1459924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="129" startId="2.[151,264,1585,1608]" targetBox="[316,1276,453,1557]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1585,1669]" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,316,1585,1608]" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">FIGURES 1–6.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Tol &amp; Bedjanič, 2018" authorityName="Tol &amp; Bedjanič" authorityYear="2018" box="[325,591,1587,1608]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seramensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[325,591,1587,1608]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">Drepanosticta seramensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[599,682,1586,1607]" pageId="2" pageNumber="129" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[599,682,1586,1607]" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(1) head and thorax, lateral view [holotype male]; (2) anal appendages, ventrolateral view [holotype male]; (3) anal appendages, dorsal view [holotype male]; (4) head and thorax, lateral view [allotype female]; (5) ovipositor, lateral view [allotype female]; (6) wings [holotype male].
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1714,2027]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,151,1005]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="130" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis box="[199,280,1714,1739]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[299,369,1714,1739]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1585,1608]" captionTargetBox="[316,1276,453,1557]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[302,1284,445,1564]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Drepanosticta seramensis sp. nov. (1) head and thorax, lateral view [holotype male]; (2) anal appendages, ventrolateral view [holotype male]; (3) anal appendages, dorsal view [holotype male]; (4) head and thorax, lateral view [allotype female]; (5) ovipositor, lateral view [allotype female]; (6) wings [holotype male]." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1459924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Pronotum erect, without conspicuous processes, predominantly brown; anterior lobe with paired oblong pale cream markings, lateral corners of this lobe dark brown, rest brown; median lobe middlebrown, flat; lateral lobes dark brown, brownish black in ventro-lateral corners; posterior lobe flat, dark brown, with small, but distinct and somewhat erect, triangular projections in lateral corners (
<figureCitation box="[1045,1134,1821,1846]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1751,1774]" captionTargetBox="[164,1418,1073,1678]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,1057,1731]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Drepanosticta species. (7–8) D. amboinensis van Tol: (7) superior appendage, left lateral view; (8) inferior appendage, ventral view. (9–11) D. seramensis sp. nov.: (9) superior appendage, left lateral view; (10) inferior appendage, ventral view; (11) pronotum, dorsal view (Figs 7–8, JvT 23548, Figs. 9–11, JvT 32749, holotype male)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1459926/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). Synthorax dark brown; mesepimeron distinctly darker, and metepimeron somewhat paler than other parts. Legs dirty yellow, with narrow, but distinct dark annulae distally on all femora; bases of tibiae somewhat darker than rest of legs. Wings hyaline, venation brown (
<figureCitation box="[344,414,1930,1955]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1585,1608]" captionTargetBox="[316,1276,453,1557]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[302,1284,445,1564]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Drepanosticta seramensis sp. nov. (1) head and thorax, lateral view [holotype male]; (2) anal appendages, ventrolateral view [holotype male]; (3) anal appendages, dorsal view [holotype male]; (4) head and thorax, lateral view [allotype female]; (5) ovipositor, lateral view [allotype female]; (6) wings [holotype male]." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1459924/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
); Arculus just distal to Ax2; Px in fore wing 15½ (the last one incomplete), in hind wing 14½ (the last one incomplete); R4+5 at subnodus; IR3 arising halfway first cell distal to subnodus; Ab vein meeting Ac at hind margin of wings (Y sessile); CuP reaching hind margin of fore wing at level of Px4, in hind wing at level of Px5; ten cells between Arculus and place where CuP meets hind margin of hind wing; pterostigma rather pale, oblique, wider than high.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis box="[199,312,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Brown, posteriorly somewhat darker; paler markings anteriorly on segments as follows: one-tenth of segment 3, one-eighth of segment 4, one-sixth of segment 5 and one-fifth of segment 6. Anal appendages with superiors brown, inferiors dirty yellow (
<figureCitation box="[596,702,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1585,1608]" captionTargetBox="[316,1276,453,1557]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[302,1284,445,1564]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Drepanosticta seramensis sp. nov. (1) head and thorax, lateral view [holotype male]; (2) anal appendages, ventrolateral view [holotype male]; (3) anal appendages, dorsal view [holotype male]; (4) head and thorax, lateral view [allotype female]; (5) ovipositor, lateral view [allotype female]; (6) wings [holotype male]." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1459924/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Figs. 2, 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[714,772,296,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1751,1774]" captionTargetBox="[164,1418,1073,1678]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,1057,1731]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Drepanosticta species. (7–8) D. amboinensis van Tol: (7) superior appendage, left lateral view; (8) inferior appendage, ventral view. (9–11) D. seramensis sp. nov.: (9) superior appendage, left lateral view; (10) inferior appendage, ventral view; (11) pronotum, dorsal view (Figs 7–8, JvT 23548, Figs. 9–11, JvT 32749, holotype male)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1459926/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">9, 10</figureCitation>
); superiors basal two-fifths robust, distal three-fifths dorsoventrally compressed, elongate club-shaped, tip rounded, a distinct dorsal tubercle at two-fifths from base; inferiors in ventral view rather robust, diverging, distal part of each appendage compressed and tip curved inward, more similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lieftinck" authorityYear="1938" box="[264,422,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moluccana">
<emphasis box="[264,422,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">D. moluccana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Buru than to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="van Tol" authorityYear="2007" box="[637,811,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amboinensis">
<emphasis box="[637,811,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">D. amboinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[879,967,404,429]" name="Indonesia" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Ambon</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1005]" box="[199,1272,439,464]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,374,439,464]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Measurements</emphasis>
(including appendages) (mm). Total length 43.5, abdomen 36.0, hindwing 24.0.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,487,476,501]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">
Variation in 
<typeStatus box="[362,482,476,501]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">paratypes</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
One mature male: abdomen 
<quantity box="[845,932,476,501]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="3" pageNumber="130" unit="mm" value="36.0">36 mm</quantity>
, hindwing 
<quantity box="[1070,1179,476,501]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" pageId="3" pageNumber="130" unit="mm" value="22.5">22.5 mm</quantity>
. Other males teneral, hindwing 
<quantity box="[264,388,512,536]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.15" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="2.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="130" unit="mm" value="21.5" valueMax="22.0" valueMin="21.0">21–22 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,548,573]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Female.</emphasis>
Coloration of head and thorax similar to the male (
<figureCitation box="[872,941,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1585,1608]" captionTargetBox="[316,1276,453,1557]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[302,1284,445,1564]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Drepanosticta seramensis sp. nov. (1) head and thorax, lateral view [holotype male]; (2) anal appendages, ventrolateral view [holotype male]; (3) anal appendages, dorsal view [holotype male]; (4) head and thorax, lateral view [allotype female]; (5) ovipositor, lateral view [allotype female]; (6) wings [holotype male]." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1459924/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
), somewhat better defined than in 
<typeStatus box="[1331,1433,548,573]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">holotype</typeStatus>
. Wings as in male, Px in forewing 14½ (or 15), hindwing 14½; R4+5 arising at (forewing) or just anterior (hindwing) to nodus; IR3 arising halfway first cell distal to subnodus; Ab vein meeting Ac just before hind margin of wing (Y shortly stalked); CuP reaching hind margin of forewing at level of Px4, in hindwing at level of Px5; nine cells between Arculus and place where CuP meets hind margin of hind wing. Pterostigma middle brown. Abdomen stouter than in male. Valves and terebra short, not surpassing level of anal appendages (
<figureCitation box="[1247,1315,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1585,1608]" captionTargetBox="[316,1276,453,1557]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[302,1284,445,1564]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Drepanosticta seramensis sp. nov. (1) head and thorax, lateral view [holotype male]; (2) anal appendages, ventrolateral view [holotype male]; (3) anal appendages, dorsal view [holotype male]; (4) head and thorax, lateral view [allotype female]; (5) ovipositor, lateral view [allotype female]; (6) wings [holotype male]." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1459924/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">
Measurements (variation of 
<typeStatus box="[515,622,765,789]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">paratypes</typeStatus>
in brackets). Abdomen 33 (other specimens not measured), hindwing 23 (22–23).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="130" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,836,861]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Lieftinck" authorityName="Lieftinck" authorityYear="1938" box="[541,812,836,861]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moluccana">
<emphasis box="[541,701,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">D. moluccana</emphasis>
Lieftinck
</taxonomicName>
and very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="van Tol" authorityName="van Tol" authorityYear="2007" box="[1049,1324,836,861]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amboinensis">
<emphasis box="[1049,1225,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">D. amboinensis</emphasis>
van Tol
</taxonomicName>
; the male differs from the latter species by its sharp, somewhat erect lateral edges of the posterior lobe of the pronotum, its more elongate ventral club of the superior anal appendages (rather similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lieftinck" authorityYear="1938" box="[1047,1207,908,933]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moluccana">
<emphasis box="[1047,1207,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">D. moluccana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas it is more triangular in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="van Tol" authorityYear="2007" box="[297,472,943,968]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amboinensis">
<emphasis box="[297,472,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">D. amboinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and its more robust and subterminally constricted inferior appendages as compared with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="van Tol" authorityYear="2007" box="[207,382,980,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amboinensis">
<emphasis box="[207,382,980,1005]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">D. amboinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[397,519,980,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1751,1774]" captionTargetBox="[164,1418,1073,1678]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,1057,1731]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Drepanosticta species. (7–8) D. amboinensis van Tol: (7) superior appendage, left lateral view; (8) inferior appendage, ventral view. (9–11) D. seramensis sp. nov.: (9) superior appendage, left lateral view; (10) inferior appendage, ventral view; (11) pronotum, dorsal view (Figs 7–8, JvT 23548, Figs. 9–11, JvT 32749, holotype male)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1459926/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Figs. 7–11</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1459926/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="130" startId="3.[151,264,1751,1774]" targetBox="[164,1418,1073,1678]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1751,1842]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,327,1751,1774]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">FIGURES 7–11.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laidlaw" authorityYear="1917" box="[334,478,1753,1774]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[334,478,1753,1774]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Drepanosticta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. (7–8) 
<taxonomicName authority="van Tol" authorityName="van Tol" authorityYear="2007" box="[636,884,1752,1774]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amboinensis">
<emphasis box="[636,795,1752,1774]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">D. amboinensis</emphasis>
van Tol
</taxonomicName>
: (7) superior appendage, left lateral view; (8) inferior appendage, ventral view. (9–11) 
<taxonomicName authority="Tol &amp; Bedjanič, 2018" authorityName="Tol &amp; Bedjanič" authorityYear="2018" box="[493,639,1786,1807]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seramensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[493,639,1786,1807]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">D. seramensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[649,732,1786,1807]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[649,732,1786,1807]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
: (9) superior appendage, left lateral view; (10) inferior appendage, ventral view; (11) pronotum, dorsal view (Figs 7–8, JvT 23548, Figs. 9–11, JvT 32749, holotype male).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="131" pageId="3" pageNumber="130" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1926,2023]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="131" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,496,1926,1951]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
Seram (
<collectingCountry box="[588,701,1926,1951]" name="Indonesia" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Moluccas</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[712,826,1926,1951]" name="Indonesia" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
). The distribution of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1099,1250,1926,1951]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Platystictidae</taxonomicName>
of the 
<collectingCountry box="[1327,1436,1926,1951]" name="Indonesia" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Moluccas</collectingCountry>
is presented in 
<figureCitation box="[323,406,1962,1987]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1739,1761]" captionTargetBox="[340,1240,1030,1703]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[340,1247,1020,1718]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 12. Distribution of Drepanosticta species of the Moluccas (records from Sulawesi and New Guinea not indicated). After van Tol (2007), new records with coloured symbols." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1459928/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
. Based on a figure in van Tol (2007), we have added the records of two recently described species (
<taxonomicName authority="Theischinger et al., 2015" authorityName="Theischinger et al." authorityYear="2015" box="[248,718,1998,2023]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pararudicula">
<emphasis box="[248,431,1998,2023]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">D. pararudicula</emphasis>
Theischinger 
<emphasis box="[592,648,1998,2023]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">et al.</emphasis>
, 2015
</taxonomicName>
from Halmahera, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kovacs &amp; Theischinger, 2015" authorityName="Kovacs &amp; Theischinger" authorityYear="2015" box="[972,1436,1998,2023]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batanta">
<emphasis box="[972,1093,1998,2023]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">D. batanta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[1100,1436,1998,2023]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130" refId="ref3152" refString="Kovacs, T., Theischinger, G., Juhasz, P. &amp; Danyik, T. (2015) Odonata from Batanta (Indonesia, West Papua) with description of three new species. Folia historico-naturalia Musei Matraensis, 39, 17 - 29." type="journal article">Kóvacs &amp; Theischinger, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from Batanta) (see Kóvacs 
<emphasis box="[468,528,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="131">et al.</emphasis>
at. 2015), and of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Selys)" authorityName="Selys" baseAuthorityName="Selys" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[740,982,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="4" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auriculata">
<emphasis box="[740,894,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="131">D. auriculata</emphasis>
(Selys)
</taxonomicName>
(previously reported from the northern Bird’s Head Peninsula of New 
<collectingCountry box="[498,583,188,213]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="4" pageNumber="131">Guinea</collectingCountry>
), and the record of 
<taxonomicName authority="Tol &amp; Bedjanič, 2018" authorityName="Tol &amp; Bedjanič" authorityYear="2018" box="[800,959,189,212]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="4" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seramensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[800,959,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="131">D. seramensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[965,1025,189,212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="131" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(with red symbol).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="131">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tol &amp; Bedjanič" authorityYear="2018" box="[199,494,225,248]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Drepanosticta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="4" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seramensis">
<emphasis box="[199,494,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="131">Drepanosticta seramensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected on various small streams in and around Manusela National Park, between 20 and 
<quantity box="[334,405,260,284]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="131" unit="m" value="400.0">400 m</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[420,502,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1639,1661]" captionTargetBox="[340,1246,195,1580]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[340,1246,195,1580]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 13. Small stream in forest along path to Kanikeh village, Manusela National Park, Seram. Locality of Drepanosticta seramensis. Photo M. Bedjanič." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1459930/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="131">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
